C3: 14<br>
Manasong: 20 (pumping bard - purely an estimate)<br>
BAotR: 6<br>
MC: 3<br>
SP: 7<br>
Innate+Y5: 5 (not counting sitting/horse/and only partially counting the use of Y5).<br>
<br>
Total: 70 mana/tick<br>
<br>
CH costs: 316 mana with scm3.<br>
<br>
So, to cast CH every 15 sec (thats an insanely fast CHO) the cleric will be in the hole with 111 mana/15 sec - or 444 mana per min *with* max current AA skills and FT15. With c3 on thats around 10 mins for a well geared cleric. <br>
<br>
To cast once every 20 sec the cleric will last around 18 mins and at 27 sec (insanely slow) the cleric breaks even. <br>
<br>
Note, this isnt using MW, the new ModRod2 or twitch.<br>
<br>
Then add the upgrades from PoP:<br>
- BAotR: +2<br>
- C3: +4<br>
- SP: +2<br>
- Bard: +7<br>
- Adv. SCM making CH cost 296 instead<br>
<br>
and a fully decked cleric can run a 15 sec CH for 12 mins and break even around 21 sec. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4264>Mikar of the Nexus</a><br>High Priest of Brell<br><a href=http://companions.windsofstorm.net/>The Companions</a><br>The Tribunal 

